      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(ui): preserve live tool stream order",
        "body": "Fixes #92122\n\n## What Problem This Solves\nLive WebChat tool cards were reordered incorrectly when a tool event timestamp was older than the assistant stream segment that introduced that tool call. The timestamp-only sorter could place tool cards before their causal assistant text.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\nThread optional `toolCallId` metadata through chat stream segment types so the renderer can keep the matching tool card after its causal assistant text while preserving ordinary timestamp ordering. Adds regression coverage for the delayed/live timestamp race and same-millisecond multi-segment ordering.\n\n## User Impact\nWebChat tool cards now appear in correct causal order — after the assistant text that invoked them — even when tool event timestamps are slightly earlier than the stream segment timestamp.\n\n## Evidence\n\n**Vitest:**\n```\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/chat/build-chat-items.test.ts --run\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/views/chat.test.ts --run\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/controllers/chat.test.ts --run\n```\n\n**Browser proof:** [WebChat live tool ordering screenshot](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Pick-cat/openclaw/proof/pr-93184-webchat-tool-ordering/proof.png)",
